text: Illinois’s annual house price growth has trailed the US average each quarter since 2009.
Average private-sector weekly earnings range from Mississippi's $768 to DC's $1,691.
Alaska’s December unemployment rate (6.1%) was the highest of any state.
Wyoming’s GDP fell 3.2% since last year. It was the largest annual decline of any state in Q3 2019.
Idaho and Utah had the largest increases in house prices between Q4 2018 and Q4 2019.
Virginia was one of 22 states with a decade-low unemployment rate in December.
In December, only four states saw a year-over-year decline in private employment.
Utah’s year-over-year job growth has exceeded the US average each month since April 2010.
Between December 2018 and 2019, state and local public employment fell in 12 states.
